column2: The temperature is 80 degrees with a hazy bright sun.
Temp 85 F- do believe wind + sun greatly influence these readings and boat traffic.
Loons taking off from the water- we have a nesting family this year for the first time in 10 years
Warm- still conditions- clear blue sky.  Lake level: very high
Great day-no wind- still clear water.
Lots of boats and jet skiers.
Hot- bright and windy. The temperature is 83 degrees.
Three immature loons calling- great day- sunny- still bright.
Water is high- rushing through outlet- sedges and grasses in area on eastern shore not yet grown.
Wind came up and the water became rough.
No wind- 70 degrees  sea gulls (herring) and very clear- we need more line.
Two bald eagles in a tree.
Eagle swooped down and grabbed northern pike from fisherman's hands.
Eagle and nest and one loon.
More plants around east end; more emergent plants
Immature loon; All emergents dead.  This basin is not stratified.
